# AOCL-DLP Examples

This directory contains example programs demonstrating how to use the AOCL-DLP (AMD Optimized Computing Library for Deep Learning Primitives) library.

## Directory Structure

```
examples/
├── CMakeLists.txt       # Top-level build configuration
└── classic/             # Classic API examples
    ├── CMakeLists.txt   # Classic examples build configuration
    ├── README.md        # Detailed classic examples documentation
    ├── src/             # Source files for all classic examples
    └── [executables]    # Pre-built example binaries
```

## Pre-built Examples

Pre-built example executables are available in the subdirectories and can be run directly. See the README.md files in each subdirectory for details.

## Building All Examples

To rebuild all examples from this top-level directory:

```bash
# Create a build directory
mkdir build && cd build

# Configure using the shared library (default)
cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/path/to/aocl-dlp/install ..
make

# OR configure using the static library
cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/path/to/aocl-dlp/install -DUSE_STATIC_LIBRARY=ON ..
make

# Build specific examples
make simple_gemm_f32 version
```

## Building Individual Example Categories

You can also build examples from their respective subdirectories:

```bash
# Build classic examples
cd classic
mkdir build && cd build
cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/path/to/aocl-dlp/install ..
make
```

## Configuration Options

- **USE_STATIC_LIBRARY** (default: OFF): Link examples with the static AOCL-DLP library
  - Set to ON for static linking: `-DUSE_STATIC_LIBRARY=ON`
  - Set to OFF for shared library linking (default)

- **CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH**: Path to the AOCL-DLP installation directory
  - Required if AOCL-DLP is installed in a non-standard location

## Requirements

- AOCL-DLP library version @PROJECT_VERSION@ or compatible
- C compiler with C11 support
- CMake @CMAKE_MINIMUM_REQUIRED_VERSION@ or later
- OpenMP support (typically provided by the compiler)

## Example Categories

### Classic API Examples (`classic/`)

Examples using the classic AOCL-DLP API for low-precision GEMM operations:
- Basic GEMM operations (FP32, BF16, INT8)
- Matrix reordering and packing
- Batch GEMM operations
- Post-operations (bias, ReLU, quantization)
- Eltwise operations

For detailed information about each example, see `classic/README.md`.

